  "sections": {
    "Description": "The Spider Leader starts with two spiderling eggs that hatch before the player turn. Each time the spider leader moves, it will throw two spiderling eggs onto random locations around the map. Unlike normal spiders these eggs do not immobilise adjacent units.\nUnlike all other leaders Spider Leaders can only appear in the boss mission of an island. On Unfairdifficulty, they cannot appear on regular missions in the fourth island.",
    "Strategy": "Weapons that can effectively spread damage or displace multiple targets are highly recommended when facing the Spider Leader. The multiple eggs spawned at the beginning of each turn can create obstacles for your grounded mechs, and its multiple spawnedSpiderlingscan become troublesome if left unchecked as they spread through the map.\nIn particular, look for weapons such asMissile BarrageorElectric Whip, which can take out the Spiderlings while also damaging the Spider Leader and other enemies.",
    "Trivia": "  - Before Version 1.2.78 the Spider Leader could appear on regular missions of the fourth island in Unfair mode."
  },
  "full_text": "Spider Leader\nDetails\nHealth\n6\nMove\n2\nSystems\nPlentiful Offspring\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nThrow out 2-3\nSpiderling eggs\n.\nSpecial\nMassive\n: Massive units can walk in Water (but Water will prevent attacking or repairing).\nTemplate:Jumper\nThe\nSpider Leader\nis one of the Boss\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nThe Spider Leader starts with two spiderling eggs that hatch before the player turn. Each time the spider leader moves, it will throw two spiderling eggs onto random locations around the map. Unlike normal spiders these eggs do not immobilise adjacent units.\nUnlike all other leaders Spider Leaders can only appear in the boss mission of an island. On Unfair\ndifficulty\n, they cannot appear on regular missions in the fourth island.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nWeapons that can effectively spread damage or displace multiple targets are highly recommended when facing the Spider Leader. The multiple eggs spawned at the beginning of each turn can create obstacles for your grounded mechs, and its multiple spawned\nSpiderlings\ncan become troublesome if left unchecked as they spread through the map.\nIn particular, look for weapons such as\nMissile Barrage\nor\nElectric Whip\n, which can take out the Spiderlings while also damaging the Spider Leader and other enemies.\nTrivia\n[\n]\nBefore Version 1.2.78 the Spider Leader could appear on regular missions of the fourth island in Unfair mode.\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\n•\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n•\nAlpha Blob\n•\nSpiderling Egg\n•\nSpiderling\n•\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n•\nAlpha Spore\n•\nVicious Spore\n•\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n•\nFirefly Leader\n•\nHornet Leader\n•\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) •\nPsion Abomination\n•\nScorpion Leader\n•\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n•\nBouncer Leader\n•\nCentipede Leader\n•\nCrab Leader\n•\nGastropod Leader\n•\nMosquito Leader\n•\nPlasmodia Leader\n•\nScarab Leader\n•\nStarfish Leader\n•\nTumblebug Leader"
